info.description: This is the REST API description of SHOGun
info.title: SHOGun Boot REST-API

clientConfig.description: The configuration to be considered by the client/application which may include all specific configurations required by the project.

layerConfig.description: The definition of layer configurations. This may be used to set application specific configurations for any layers in the given application.

layerTree.description: The tree shaped configuration entry of the applications table of contents.

modified.description: The timestamp of the last modification.

stateOnly.description: Whether the application configuration is considered as state or not. A state may be used as snapshot of a given application.

toolConfig.description: The definition of tool configurations. This may be used to set application specific configurations for any tools in the given application, e.g. the visibility or the layers the tool should work on.

active.description: Whether the file is considered as active or not.

fileUuid.description: The (auto assigned) UUID of the file.

modified.description: The timestamp of the last modification.

keycloakId.description: The internal Keycloak ID of the group.

keycloakRepresentation.description: The group details stored in the associated Keycloak entity.

modified.description: The timestamp of the last modification.

active.description: Whether the file is considered as active or not.

fileUuid.description: The (auto assigned) UUID of the file.

height.description: The (original) height of the image file.

modified.description: The timestamp of the last modification.

width.description: The (original) width of the image file.

clientConfig.description: The configuration of the layer which should be used to define client specific aspects of the layer. This may include the name, the visible resolution range, search configurations or similiar.

features.description: Custom features for the layers that aren't available in the datasource. This might be used for custom draw layers or similiar. It's advised to store the features using the GeoJSON format.

modified.description: The timestamp of the last modification.

name.description: The internal name of the layer.

sourceConfig.description: The configuration of the datasource of the layer, e.g. the URL of the server, the name or the grid configuration.

type.description: The type of the layer. Currently one of `TileWMS`, `VectorTile`, `WFS`, `WMS`, `WMTS` or `XYZ`.

clientConfig.description: The configuration of the user which should be used to define client specific aspects of the user. This may include the locale set by the user, the last application visited by the user or similiar.

details.description: Custom user details that aren't stored inside the Keycloak representation.

keycloakId.description: The internal Keycloak ID of the user.

keycloakRepresentation.description: The user details stored in the associated Keycloak entity.

modified.description: The timestamp of the last modification.
